<% content_for :title, spanish? ? "Sobre mi - Angel Mora" : "About - Angel Mora" %>
<%# BRAND artifact: Gallery Space register; display title, mono metadata, hard rules, no rounded elements. %>

<%
  paragraphs = if spanish?
    [
      "Siempre me ha apasionado programar. Tuve mi primera computadora a los 10 anos y desde entonces he aprendido rompiendo cosas, arreglandolas y entendiendo como funcionan los sistemas. Durante la universidad pase muchas horas en Linux, leyendo sobre distros y el movimiento Open Source. En 2017 empece con Ruby y Jekyll escribiendo un blog llamado disonancias.org; desde ahi me acerque a JavaScript, GitHub y a la idea de publicar conocimiento como software.",
      "Trabaje en un Call Center para AT&T, donde aprendi mucho sobre debugging en el navegador y consultas SQL complejas. Mis primeros retos tecnicos serios tambien venian de automatizar escritura con Pandoc y Bash. El filesystem Unix y algo de scripting me ensenaron que los lenguajes de programacion son formas de conversar con una maquina muy poderosa.",
      "En 2019 llegue a mi primer trabajo formal como Data Analyst usando R, Python y herramientas OSINT para analisis criminal. Ese trabajo me mostro el valor de tener aplicaciones que aseguran, organizan y vuelven accesible investigacion compleja.",
      "En 2023 termine un Cybersecurity Bootcamp de EdX que me ayudo a obtener la certificacion CompTIA Security+. Despues segui trabajando en equipos internacionales, mejorando monolitos Rails, sistemas internos, automatizaciones y productos donde el conocimiento se convierte en infraestructura.",
      "Paso mucho tiempo mejorando mis skills en Obsidian y desarrollando proyectos para Knowledge Base Networking. Me gustan los editores de texto old-school como Vim y Emacs, los proyectos GIS y The Rails Way. Si mi perfil te parece interesante, escribeme."
    ]
  else
    [
      "I've always been passionate about programming. I got my first computer when I was 10 and have been breaking, fixing, and learning systems ever since. During college I spent hours in Linux, reading about distros and the Open Source Software Movement. A few years later, in 2017, I started with Ruby and Jekyll, writing a blog called disonancias.org; from there I fell in love with JavaScript, GitHub, and the idea of publishing knowledge as software.",
      "I worked in a Call Center for AT&T and learned a lot about debugging the browser and performing complex SQL queries. My first serious technical challenges were also related to automating writing with Pandoc and Bash. The Unix filesystem and some Bash scripting helped me understand that programming languages are ways to interact with the powerful system a computer is.",
      "In 2019 I landed my first formal job as a Data Analyst using R, Python, and OSINT tools for crime analysis. That job showed me the value of applications that secure, organize, and make complex research accessible.",
      "In 2023 I finished a Cybersecurity Bootcamp from EdX that helped me earn my CompTIA Security+ certification. After that I continued working with international product teams, improving Rails monoliths, internal systems, automation, and products where knowledge becomes infrastructure.",
      "I spend a lot of time improving my Obsidian skills and developing projects for Knowledge Base Networking. I like old-school text editors like Vim and Emacs, GIS projects, and The Rails Way. If you find my profile interesting, don't hesitate to reach out."
    ]
  end

  social_links = [
    ["Twitter", "https://twitter.com/angelmoradev"],
    ["GitHub", "https://github.com/angel-mora"],
    ["LinkedIn", "https://linkedin.com/in/angelmoradev"],
    ["Email", "mailto:angelmomaa@gmail.com"]
  ]
%>

<section class="border-b border-black bg-white py-16 dark:border-white dark:bg-black sm:py-24">
  <div class="brand-container brand-grid">
    <div class="lg:col-span-3">
      <span class="brand-section-marker"><span class="brand-section-marker__number">01</span> <%= spanish? ? "Sobre mi" : "About" %></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lg:col-span-8 lg:col-start-5">
      <p class="brand-kicker"><%= spanish? ? "Filosofo / programador / Mexico" : "Philosopher / programmer / Mexico" %></p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-4xl font-display text-5xl font-bold leading-none tracking-[-0.05em] text-black dark:text-white sm:text-7xl">
        <%= spanish? ? "Soy Angel Mora, filosofo y programador." : "I'm Angel Mora, philosopher and programmer." %>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 font-mono text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
        <%= spanish? ? "6+ anos de experiencia" : "6+ years of experience" %>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="bg-white py-16 dark:bg-black sm:py-24">
  <div class="brand-container brand-grid">
    <aside class="lg:col-span-3">
      <div class="border-2 border-black p-6 dark:border-white">
        <div class="flex aspect-square items-center justify-center border border-black dark:border-white">
          <span class="font-display text-7xl font-bold tracking-[-0.05em] text-black dark:text-white">AM</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-3 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.1em]">
          <% social_links.each do |label, href| %>
            <%= link_to label, href, class: "block text-zinc-600 hover:text-black hover:underline decoration-brand decoration-2 underline-offset-4 dark:text-zinc-400 dark:hover:text-white", target: (href.start_with?("http") ? "_blank" : nil), rel: (href.start_with?("http") ? "noopener" : nil) %>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </aside>
    <div class="font-reading text-lg leading-8 text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300 lg:col-span-7 lg:col-start-5">
      <% paragraphs.each do |paragraph| %>
        <p class="mt-6 first:mt-0"><%= paragraph %></p>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
